[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ceredigion Museum's £916k grant for shop and tourist hub

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A mid Wales museum is to get a new shop, tourist information centre and cafe funded by the Heritage Lottery Fund.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Ceredigion Museum, in Aberystwyth, will also get new equipment for the Coliseum auditorium from the £916,200 grant.
Council leader Ellen ap Gwynn said the work would help attract more people to the "hidden gem".
The work is part of a wider £1.3m project.
